            <description><![CDATA[<p>Release date: 2026-05-14</p>
<h2 id="new">New</h2>
<h2 id="improvements">Improvements</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Improved license recovery after reinstalling
NameQuick.</strong> Self-Managed licenses can now reconnect to the same
Mac more reliably instead of getting stuck on device activation.</li>
<li><strong>Made trial activation more reliable.</strong> NameQuick now
checks existing account access more consistently before asking you to
start checkout again.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="bug-fixes">Bug Fixes</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Fixed Self-Managed trial activation getting stuck.</strong>
Existing Self-Managed trial users should now be able to activate with
their email instead of being blocked at the license screen.</li>
<li><strong>Fixed subscription trials looping back to checkout.</strong>
Active trial accounts should now unlock from their existing account
access even when checkout confirmation is delayed.</li>
<li><strong>Fixed device activation recovery for Self-Managed
licenses.</strong> Reinstalling NameQuick on the same Mac should no
longer try to use an extra device slot when the original activation
already belongs to that Mac.</li>
<li><strong>Fixed the customer portal link in activation
recovery.</strong> The recovery action now opens the signed-in customer
portal instead of sending you to a generic page.</li>
<li><strong>Improved the message shown when an email is not
found.</strong> NameQuick now gives clearer next steps for trying
another email, starting a trial, or contacting support.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
